OL,7,FMADRID ` An unusually dry spring
OL,8,Facross parts of southern Europe could
OL,9,Fthreaten summer holidays with a
OL,10,Frepeat of last year's devastating
OL,11,Fwildfires, the head of the EU climate
OL,12,Fmonitoring service has warned.
OL,14,FSpain recorded its hottest ever April
OL,15,Fday on Thursday at 38.7C, and
OL,16,Fextreme temperatures led to the death
OL,17,Fof one horse and to another
OL,18,Fcollapsing while pulling carriages
OL,19,Fthrough Seville. The drought-hit
OL,20,Fcountry is so dry that some farmers
OL,21,Fhave opted not to plant crops.
OL,3,C'Historic' wildfires may threaten
OL,4,Csummer holidays in Europe as Spain
OL,5,Csees record 39C April day
